Two alleged drug dealers were nabbed in a Westham drug raid where police officers from the Provincial Drug and Firearm Unit searched the premises on Waltham Road and seized drugs, a firearm and ammunition, yesterday (Monday). The two suspects aged between 25 and 27 are set to appear in the Verulam Magistrate’s Court for possession of drugs. Police spokesperson, Captain Nqobile Gwala said:  “The two were arrested after they were found in possession of 115 pieces of rock cocaine, a 9mm pistol, two magazines and 27 rounds of ammunition. The value of the cocaine is R11, 500. During early November, police officers from the Provincial Drug and Firearm Unit, received intelligence of drug dealing from a premises on Waltham Road in Phoenix. Following an intensive investigation, yesterday afternoon police officers from the Provincial Drug and Firearm Unit proceeded to the premises to execute a search warrant.” “During the operation, police seized rock cocaine from two suspects’ as well as a firearm and ammunition that was found on the premises. The suspects were placed under arrest for possession of drugs while investigations concerning the firearm found on the premises, continues,” added Cpt Gwala. The KwaZulu-Natal Provincial Commissioner, Lieutenant General Khombinkosi Jula praised the Provincial Drug and Firearm Unit for their dedication in fight crime in our province.